  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Tip the macaroni into a saucepan of salted boiling water. Once the pasta is al dente, drain and rinse so that the pasta doesn’t stick together. Reserve some of the pasta water to use later."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "While the pasta is cooking, make the breadcrumbs. Break up the bread, transfer to a food processor and blitz into breadcrumbs. Grate the cheddar and set it aside. Finely chop the parsley. Melt the butter in a frying pan over a medium heat. Once sizzling, add the breadcrumbs followed by the garlic, herbs and a pinch of salt. Continue to stir over a medium-high heat for around 10 mins until golden and crispy, then set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the milk, cottage cheese, soft cheese, onion powder, mustard, cheddar and half of the Parmesan to the food processor, along with 50ml pasta water (no need to clean the processor after using it for the bread – a few crumbs won’t hurt!). Blitz until smooth to create the sauce."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat your grill. Pour the sauce into one of the pans that you just used. Cook over a low heat for a couple of minutes and season with salt and pepper to taste. Stir in the cooked pasta and the mozzarella, along with some pasta water to loosen it up, if needed."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Top with the remaining Parmesan followed by the breadcrumbs and pop it under the hot grill until melted and crispy."
    }
  ],
